==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lucernal
<hw>Lu*cer"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lucerna</ets> a lamp.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a
lamp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lucernal microscope</b></col>, <cd>a form of the
microscope in which the object is illuminated by means of a lamp, and
its image is thrown upon a plate of ground glass connected with the
instrument, or on a screen independent of it.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lucernaria</ent>⟦br⟧
